messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

- Full path:

- All HTTP methods acceptable: false

- HEAD: false
- POST: true
- OPTIONS: false
- TRACE: false
- GET: false
- PUT: false
- DELETE: false
- PATCH: false

Explanation:
- The handler method finishAndSubmitPrintRequest is annotated with @RequestMapping(value = "/consumer/printrequest/{printRequestID}/submit", method = RequestMethod.POST). There is no class-level @RequestMapping in PrintRequestController, so the full path is exactly "/consumer/printrequest/{printRequestID}/submit".
- The @RequestMapping explicitly declares method = RequestMethod.POST, so only POST is acceptable according to the code. The other HTTP methods are not declared on this mapping and therefore are considered not acceptable based on the source. (Per your instruction, implicit framework behaviors such as automatic HEAD/OPTIONS handling are not assumed.)
